CD19


Description

B-lymphocyte antigen CD19 (CD19). Functions as coreceptor for the B-cell antigen receptor complex (BCR) on B-lymphocytes. Decreases the threshold for activation of downstream signaling pathways and for triggering B-cell responses to antigens.


Clinical trials

NCT02465983 - Pancreatic Cancer
